Getting nvim up and running:
1. Install neovim
   (https://neovim.io/)
   (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/wiki/Installing-Neovim)
   dnf install -y neovim python{2,3}-neovim
2. Install pynvim
   pip install --user pynvim  # python 2
   pip3 install --user pynvim  # python 3
3. Install vim-plug
   (https://github.com/junegunn/vim-plug)
   curl -fLo ~/.local/share/nvim/site/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs \
    https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim
4. Make sure the file called init.vim is located at the path ~/.config/nvim/
5. Run nvim and install the plugins
   :PlugInstall
6. Install FZF
   (https://github.com/junegunn/fzf)
   git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/junegunn/fzf.git ~/.fzf
   ~/.fzf/install 
7. Install YouCompleteMe
   (https://github.com/Valloric/YouCompleteMe)
   cd ~/.config/nvim/plugged/YouCompleteMe
   ./install.py
8. Install flake8
   pip install --user flake8
   pip3 isntall --user flake8
   
   Tip: add this to init.vim to suppress the line length warnings:
   let g:ale_python_flake8_options = '--ignore=E501'
9. If nvim appears to have color issues, run it inside a tmux session.
   Start the tmux session like this for 256 colors:
   tmux -2
